Operators are symbols that perform operations on variables and values.

C# operators are classified into several types:

1. Arithmetic Operators

Used for mathematical operations.

Operator	Description	Example
+	Addition	5 + 2 = 7
-	Subtraction	5 - 2 = 3
*	Multiplication	5 * 2 = 10
/	Division	5 / 2 = 2
%	Modulus (remainder)	5 % 2 = 1
++	Increment	x++
--	Decrement	x--

Example:

int a = 10, b = 3;
Console.WriteLine(a + b);  // 13
Console.WriteLine(a % b);  // 1
a++;
Console.WriteLine(a);      // 11

2. Comparison Operators

Compare two values, return true or false.

Operator	Description	Example
==	Equal to	5 == 5 â†’ true
!=	Not equal to	5 != 3 â†’ true
>	Greater than	5 > 3 â†’ true
<	Less than	5 < 3 â†’ false
>=	Greater or equal	5 >= 5 â†’ true
<=	Less or equal	5 <= 3 â†’ false
3. Logical Operators

Used with boolean values.

Operator	Description	Example
&&	AND	true && false â†’ false
||	OR	`true
!	NOT	!true â†’ false
4. Assignment Operators

Assign values to variables.

Operator	Description	Example
=	Assign	x = 5
+=	Add & assign	x += 3 â†’ x = x+3
-=	Subtract & assign	x -= 2 â†’ x = x-2
*=	Multiply & assign	x *= 2 â†’ x = x*2
/=	Divide & assign	x /= 2 â†’ x = x/2
%=	Modulus & assign	x %= 3 â†’ x = x%3
5. Other Operators

Ternary Operator ?: â†’ Short if-else

int x = 10;
string result = (x > 5) ? "Greater" : "Smaller";
Console.WriteLine(result); // Greater


is Operator â†’ Check type

object obj = "Hello";
if (obj is string) Console.WriteLine("String detected");


sizeof Operator â†’ Size of a type in bytes

Console.WriteLine(sizeof(int)); // 4

ðŸ›  Example Program
using System;

namespace OperatorsDemo
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            int a = 10, b = 3;

            Console.WriteLine($"a + b = {a + b}");
            Console.WriteLine($"a - b = {a - b}");
            Console.WriteLine($"a * b = {a * b}");
            Console.WriteLine($"a / b = {a / b}");
            Console.WriteLine($"a % b = {a % b}");

            bool check = (a > b) && (b > 0);
            Console.WriteLine($"Logical AND: {check}");

            a += 5; // a = 15
            Console.WriteLine($"After += : {a}");

            string result = (a > 10) ? "Big" : "Small";
            Console.WriteLine($"Ternary result: {result}");
        }
    }
}
